1> Variable Arguments

- Java's varargs allow methods to accept any number of arguments.
- Declare using an ellipsis (...) e.g, void funt(int... nums) // now funt can take any number of integer as argument
- Internal Handling : Treated as arrays, e.g., int... nums is int[] nums.
- Placement : must be the last in the method's parameters.
- Introduced in : Java 5.
